# Finding 04 — Unauthenticated Access to Calendar Data (Student PII)

**Severity:** Critical
**OWASP:** A01 Broken Access Control
**Status:** Verified fixed

## Description
The calendar events endpoint returned all event data to any unauthenticated request, including event details containing student names and schedules. No authentication was required.

## Proof of Concept (sanitised)
```
GET https://api.example.com/backend?route=/events
(no authentication headers)

→ 200 OK
[ { "title": "[class]", "description": "[student names]", "date": "...", ... }, ... ]
```

## Impact
Student personal data (names, schedules) was freely accessible to any unauthenticated party. Under applicable data-protection law (Singapore PDPA), organisations must protect personal data with reasonable security arrangements. This exposure represented a direct data-protection compliance concern in addition to the technical risk, with potential legal and reputational consequences.

## Remediation
- Enforce authentication on the events endpoint
- Restrict access so users see only events they are associated with
- Review whether personal data needs to be stored in event descriptions at all (data minimisation)

## Verification
After remediation, the unauthenticated request returned `401 Unauthorized`. Confirmed resolved.

